snippet: Turnout in the early hours was moderate in the race, which pits a former prime minister of Hosni Mubarak against a Muslim Brotherhood candidate.
abstract: Egyptian voters cast runoff ballots for the first competitively elected leader in the country's history; last-minute grab for power by Egypt's ruling generals raise questions about whether the election will be a milestone in the transition to democracy or a facade obscuring the re-emergence of the old order.

byline.original: By DAVID D. KIRKPATRICK and KAREEM FAHIM
byline.contributor: David D. Kirkpatrick reported from Cairo, and Kareem Fahim from Menoufia, Egypt. Mayy El Sheikh contributed reporting from Cairo, and Dina Salah Amer and Liam Stack from Menoufia.
